5. PPDT me Character ki Achi "Position" kaise dikhaye
Ye sabse important hai. Story me tera main character (hero) ka role strong dikhna chahiye — examiner OLQs (Officer Like Qualities) dekhta hai:

Character ko ye position do:

Hero ko leader/initiator banao — woh idea deta hai, team ko motivate karta hai
Use age + naam + role clearly do (e.g. "Rahul, 22 saal, NCC cadet / college sports captain / trekking club leader")
Story me ye flow rakhe: Situation → Problem → Hero ka action/plan → Team effort → Positive result
OLQs jo story me dikhane hain:

Initiative, Planning & Organising, Courage, Responsibility, Teamwork, Decision-making, Stamina
Expedition wali story ka example structure (positive):

"Aman, 21, ek adventure club ka secretary tha. Club ne ek coastal cleanup-cum-trek expedition plan ki. Aman ne team banayi, route recce kiya, coast guard ko inform kiya, ration aur safety gear arrange kiya. Trek ke dauran ek member ko thoda chot lagi — Aman ne shant rehkar first aid diya aur plan adjust karke sabko safe wapas laaya. Expedition successful rahi aur sabne use appreciate kiya."

Isme planning, leadership, calm under pressure, responsibility, teamwork — sab aa gaye.

