PPDT Story Format (yaad rakh)
Pehle ye 3 cheezein likhni hoti hain, fir story:

Number of characters (kitne log)
Mood (positive/neutral)
Age, Sex, Mood of main character
Fir story: kya hua tha (past) → abhi kya kar raha hai (present) → aage kya hoga (future, positive end)
Template 1: Mountain / Trek Scene 🏔️
Main char: Arjun, 22, male, positive mood (NCC cadet / trek club leader)

Arjun apne college trekking club ka leader tha. Club ne Kedarkantha winter trek plan kiya. Usne pehle route ka recce kiya, weather check ki, team ki fitness training karwayi aur safety gear arrange kiya [Planning & Organising]. Trek ke dauran heavy snowfall shuru ho gaya aur ek member thak gaya. Arjun ne shant rehkar group ko rukne ko kaha, garam drink di aur backup route se aage badha [Decision-making, Courage]. Usne sabko motivate karte hue summit tak pahunchaaya [Leadership, Stamina]. Team safely wapas aayi aur expedition successful rahi.

Template 2: Coastal / Sea Scene 🌊
Main char: Karan, 21, male, positive mood (college sports captain)

Karan ke coastal town me beach pollution badh raha tha. Usne apne dosto ke saath ek "Clean Coast" expedition plan ki [Initiative]. Local coast guard ko inform kiya, volunteers ko organise kiya aur kaam baant diya [Organising, Teamwork]. Safai ke dauran ek bachcha tez current me phasne laga — Karan ne turant decision lekar use bachaya [Courage, Quick decision]. Expedition se beach saaf ho gaya aur logo me awareness aayi. Sabne Karan ki samajhdari ki tareef ki.

Template 3: Village / Rural Scene 🏡
Main char: Vikram, 23, male, positive mood (engineering student)

Vikram ek village ka ladka tha jahan baarish me road kharab ho jaati thi aur school band rehta tha. Usne gaon ke yuvao ki team banayi [Initiative, Leadership] aur sarpanch se baat karke material arrange kiya [Resourcefulness]. Sabne milkar shram-daan se road repair ki [Teamwork, Hard work]. Ab bacche school ja paate hain. Vikram ki is pehel se poora gaon khush hua.

Template 4: Group / Indoor or Office Scene 👥
Main char: Rohit, 24, male, positive mood (team lead)

Rohit ek tech startup me junior team lead tha. Company ko ek important project deadline pe complete karna tha par team confuse thi [Problem]. Rohit ne kaam ko parts me baanta, sabko clear role diya [Organising] aur khud raat tak ruk kar guide kiya [Responsibility, Stamina]. Ek technical problem aane par usne calm rehkar solution nikala [Effective intelligence]. Project time pe complete hua aur boss ne team ko appreciate kiya.

OLQs List (Officer Like Qualities) — har story me 4-5 dikhane ki koshish kar
Factor 1 – Planning: Effective intelligence, Reasoning, Organising ability, Power of expression
Factor 2 – Social adjustment: Cooperation, Sense of responsibility, Adaptability
Factor 3 – Social effectiveness: Initiative, Self-confidence, Speed of decision, Leadership ability, Influencing the group
Factor 4 – Dynamism: Determination, Courage, Stamina

Universal Tips (story har baar achi banegi)
Hero hamesha positive aur active ho — woh problem solve kare, victim na ho
Naam-age-role pehle line me clear kar do
Time waste mat kar — story me 1 problem + 1 solution kaafi hai
Positive ending — result acha ho, log appreciate kare
Realistic rakh — superhero type exaggeration mat kar (jaise akela 10 logo ko maar diya — ye avoid kar)
Action verbs use kar — "usne plan banaya, team banayi, decision liya, guide kiya"
